    <meta name=3D"description" content=3D"Modular arithmetic is a system of=
 arithmetic for integers, which considers the remainder. In modular arithme=
tic, numbers &quot;wrap around&quot; upon reaching a given fixed quantity (=
this given quantity is known as the modulus) to leave a remainder. Modular =
arithmetic is often tied to prime numbers, for instance, in Wilson's theore=
m, Lucas's theorem, and Hensel's lemma, and generally appears in fields lik=
e cryptography, computer science, and computer algebra. An =E2=80=A6">
