arithmetic, numbers &amp;quot;wrap around&amp;quot; upon reaching a given f=
ixed quantity (this given quantity is known as the modulus) to leave a rema=
inder. Modular arithmetic is often tied to prime numbers, for instance, in =
Wilson&amp;#x27;s theorem, Lucas&amp;#x27;s theorem, and Hensel&amp;#x27;s =
lemma, and generally appears in fields like cryptography, computer science,=
 and computer algebra. An =E2=80=A6">




